-- Rajoy to Meet Leaders to Soften Possible Bailout, Expansion Says
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-08-15T06:39:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-15/rajoy-to-meet-leaders-to-soften-possible-bailout-expansion-says.html
Spain’s Prime Minister  Mariano Rajoy 
plans to meet foreign leaders, including European Union
President Herman Van Rompuy this month, to try and soften any
terms in case the country needs a full financial bailout,
 Expansion  reported today, without citing anyone.  In September, Rajoy will also meet German Chancellor Angela Merkel, Finland’s President Sauli Niinistoe and Italian Prime
Minister Mario Monti, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  